    "body": "the spec doesn't mention the correct state. Just double check, the state we use is good based on this comment:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// The only condition that is time sensitive and may require a non-head state is\r\n  // -> Validator is active && validator has not initiated exit\r\n  // The voluntaryExit.epoch must be in the past but the validator's status may change in recent epochs.\r\n  // We dial the head state to the current epoch to get the current status of the validator. This is\r\n  // relevant on periods of many skipped slots.\r\n```\r\nthe validator_exit is rejected maybe because we hold the message for too long, up to 4 epochs\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1407\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-22 at 13 21 56\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/233766573-40777382-0a66-4a51-9ffa-bce027e726a4.png\">\r\n\r\n- I'm not sure rejecting messages are suitable although that's what the spec said, it's our bad holding the message for too long not the peer\r\n- @dapplion since we have few voluntary exit, should we prioritize `voluntary_exit` topic over `beacon_attestation` topic?\r\n",
